					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5816940#post-3785592</guid>
				<title>ARMÁ ORÚN - Army of Heaven</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5816940/spc-2922#post-3785592</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 30 Apr 2018 20:26:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>stormbreath</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3075960</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article was inspired by <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-4303639">this forum post</a> about the afterlives of different GoIs - one of which was a joke about how the Shark Punching Centre has their own version of Valhalla.</p> <p>This started as just a <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2922">SCP-2922</a> knockoff, but the <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2111">Ara Orun</a> elements bled in. It's pretty much an SPC version of both of them.</p> <p>Ara Orun translates to &quot;Citizen of Heaven&quot; (Ara being Citizen; Orun being of Heaven.) Arma Orun is a weird hybrid of languages that means something like &quot;Army of Heaven&quot;.</p> <p>Thanks to all my reviewers: stallmantic, apoplexic, golden506, sifseeker, daveyoufool, feline, floppyphoenix, monorail, multizig, Dr0Shadow and sirpudding.</p> <p>Also thanks to PeppersGhost for the nice CSS!</p> <hr /> <p>If you liked this thing and would like to read some comments about it, or check out other things I've written, head to <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/stormbreath">my author page</a> for more!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
